(B, D). A, B, habitus, dorsal view; C, D, line diagram of the meso- and metasternum; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, pygidium; G, labels. Scale bar = 1.0 mm for 2A–D and 0.5 mm for 2E, F.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">
The main forest patch of Alexandria forest is 
<quantity box="[729,802,153,179]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="361" unit="km" value="78.0">78 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[802,810,152,166]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">2</superScript>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mucina, L. &amp; Rutherford, M. C." box="[827,1146,153,180]" pageId="4" pageNumber="361" refId="ref3948" refString="Mucina, L. &amp; Rutherford, M. C. (Eds.) (2006) The Vegetation of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Strelitzia 19. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, 807 pp." type="book" year="2006">Mucina &amp; Rutherford 2006</bibRefCitation>
) and there are four other forest patches of the same 
<typeStatus box="[453,501,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">type</typeStatus>
that this species may possibly inhabit. On the basis of current knowledge this new species should be assessed as endangered B2ac(iv)—see 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[800,1395,225,251]" pageId="4" pageNumber="361" refId="ref3832" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2014) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 11. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedList- Guidelines. pdf. (accessed 27 September 2019)" type="book" year="2014">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2014)</bibRefCitation>
for an explanation of the criteria.
</paragraph>
